    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="974"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thieriot</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 44.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that I have received
                    from the minister of foreign affairs a note advising me that payment has been
                    made in London of the amount awarded by the Berne Court of Arbitration in the
                    Lourenço Marquez Railway affair, with the interest thereon in addition.</p>
                <p>I have inclosed herewith a translation of the note referred to, and I have the
                    honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. H. Thieriot</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">In Charge of the Affairs of the Legation.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Arroqo</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Thieriot</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                    >Lisbon</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-23">
                                <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I beg to inform your excellency that His Majesty’s Government made a deposit
                        at the agency of the Comptoir National d’Escompte, in London, on the morning
                        of the 21st instant, pursuant to the final award of the court of arbitration
                        at Berne, payable to the order of the Government of the United States of
                        North America, and to that of Her Britannic Majesty, and as a complete
                        discharge from all responsibility on the part of Portugal, a sum equal to
                        the indemnity by the aforesaid court, with the additional amount of interest
                        at 5 per cent from the 25th June, 1889, to the 21st of the present month,
                        the date of payment.</p>
                    <p>I embrace this opportunity to renew, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">oad A. Arroqo.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
